  "response": "Ambrose Bierce's death remains shrouded in mystery. He disappeared in late 1913 or early 1914, likely in Mexico, where he had gone to observe the Mexican Revolution. Bierce was last seen in Chihuahua, Mexico, in December 1913. He sent a final letter from there, dated December 26, 1913, and after that, there was no further trace of him. \n\nThe exact circumstances of his death are unknown, but several theories exist. Some speculate he was killed in the fighting, while others suggest he was executed by a revolutionary faction. Another theory is that he took his own life, as he had expressed plans to do so in earlier letters. However, there is no conclusive evidence to confirm any of these possibilities. Bierce's disappearance and presumed death have become legendary, adding to his enigmatic legacy.",
